            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-24T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-24T03:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/2–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-24T16:00:00+08:00">February 24, 1948—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 25—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Wei Li-huang, who enjoys the acquaintance of General Marshall, requests
                    following message be delivered to Secretary: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Am appealing to you to assist me in every way possible in my effort hold
                            North east. Was sent Northeast too late hold area with forces <pb facs="0027" n="17" xml:id="pg_17"/> and equipment now at my
                            disposal. Desperately need ammunition for present troops and weapons and
                            ammunition for Northeastern People’s Milita and cargo planes move
                            equipment and supplies into Mukden. Without your support and American
                            assistance I do not believe I shall be able hold Manchuria, but with
                            them, together with additional troops from intramural China, I am
                            confident I can restore communications in and drive Communists from
                            south Manchuria.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
